  [33m> Edit[0m(new_string='## Double-Agent TDD\n\nD.U.H. natively supports a Double-Agent TDD flow modeled after red-green-refactor pair-programming. Trigger it from the REPL with `/tdd <description>`. \n\nTwo cooperating agents (Driver and Navigator) will collaborate to implement the feature:\n1. **Navigator** drafts a test spec.\n2. **Driver** writes a failing test (RED).\n3. **Driver** writes minimum code to pass the test (GREEN).\n4. **Navigator** proposes a refactor.\n5. **Driver** applies the refactor.\n6. **Navigator** validates the refactoring and test output.\n\nExample:\n```\n> /tdd add division to the calculator app, handling divide-by-zero properly\n```\nD.U.H. handles the entire lifecycle sequentially and safely.\n\n## Security', file_path='/Users/nomind/Code/Tengu/tengu-cockpit/benchmarks/double-agent-tdd/worktrees/duh-gemini-3.1/README.md')
  [33m> Bash[0m(command='ls -1 docs/wiki')
